## hex2_AMD64_darwin.hex0 — hand-rolled hex0 source that assembles to a
## runnable Darwin Mach-O hex2-darwin binary.  Replaces
## scripts/stage0/phase2-amd64-hex2.pl entirely.
##
## Layout (file offsets):
##   0x000-0x3FF  Mach-O header (1024 bytes).  __TEXT at 0x600000 size
##                0x800000, __DATA at 0xE00000 size 0x1000000, __LINKEDIT
##                at 0x1800000, entry point 0x400.  Note __DATA is 16 MiB
##                here vs 1 MiB in phase1 — hex2 needs a bigger heap for
##                its label table.
##   0x400-0x98B  Darwin-ported hex2 body, with all RIP-rel32 disps
##                baked for write_buffer = 0xE00000 and scratch_slot
##                addresses, plus a 64-bit `mov rax, 0xE00000` injected
##                in place of the SYS_BRK malloc primitive (Darwin
##                doesn't expose brk; we point at the pre-mapped __DATA).
##
## Build:  hex0 hex2_AMD64_darwin.hex0 hex2-darwin
##         dd if=/dev/zero of=hex2-darwin bs=1 count=1 seek=25165823 conv=notrunc
##         sign hex2-darwin
##
## Maintainer regenerates via scripts/stage0/regen-hex2-darwin.sh
## whenever upstream stage0Sources/AMD64/hex2_linker_AMD64.hex0 changes.

